File: President Cyril Ramaphosa has announced that the unabridged certificate requirement will be abolished this is for children entering South Africa from abroad. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has announced that the unabridged certificate requirement will be abolished for children entering South Africa from abroad. READ: South Africa experiences a decline in tourism The scrapping is so as to attract more tourists, as well as skilled workers. Ramaphosa said it will make it easier for them to come to South Africa.